UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1004
1 (d) Is a resident of Kentucky who is a uniformed-service voter as defined in KRS
2 117A.010 confined to a military base on election day and during the days of
3 no-excuse in-person absentee voting;
4 (e) Is in her last trimester of pregnancy;
5 (f) Has not been declared mentally disabled by a court of competent jurisdiction
6 and, due to age, disability, or illness, is not able to appear at the polls on
7 election day and during the days of no-excuse in-person absentee voting;
8 (g) Is a caregiver who is providing medical or healthcare assistance to a voter
9 who is qualified to cast a ballot under paragraph (f) of this subsection;
10 (h) Is a student who temporarily resides outside the county of his or her residence
11 and will be absent from the county of his or her residence on the day of an
12 election and during the days of no-excuse in-person absentee voting;
13 (i) Any person employed in an occupation that is scheduled to work during all
14 days and all hours, which shall include commute time, the polls are open on
15 election day and during the days of no-excuse in-person absentee voting;
16 (j) Any election officer tasked with election administration for the current
17 election cycle; or
18 (k) Any person prevented from voting in person at the polls on election day and
19 from casting a no-excuse in-person absentee ballot on all days no-excuse in-
20 person absentee voting is conducted because he or she will be absent from the
21 county of his or her residence during all days and all hours no-excuse in-
22 person absentee voting is conducted.
23 (3) Any voter who votes an in-person absentee or federal provisional in-person
24 absentee ballot shall provide proof of identification as defined in KRS 117.001 or
25 meet the requirements of KRS 117.228 or 117.229.
26 (4) In-person absentee voting shall be conducted in a location within the county clerk's
27 office where ballots shall be cast secretly. In-person absentee voting may occur in
