5 Public notice of the locations shall be given pursuant to KRS Chapter 424, and
6 similar notice by mail shall be given to the county chairs of the two (2) political
7 parties whose candidates polled the largest number of votes in the county at the last
8 regular election.
9 (5) Any voter qualifying to vote who receives assistance to vote in-person absentee
10 shall complete the voter assistance form required by KRS 117.255.
11 (6) Any voter qualifying to vote whose qualifications are challenged on grounds other
12 than inability to provide proof of identification by any clerk or deputy shall
13 complete an oath of voter affidavit.
14 (7) Each voter casting his or her vote in-person absentee shall sign an in-person
15 absentee ballot signature roster.
16 (8) The members of the county board of elections, or their designees who provide equal
17 representation of both political parties, may serve as precinct election officers,
18 without compensation, for all in-person absentee voting conducted. If the members
19 of the county board of elections or their designees serve as precinct election officers
20 for in-person absentee voting, they shall perform the same duties and exercise the
21 same authority as precinct election officers who serve on the day of an election. If
22 the members of the county board of elections or their designees do not serve as
23 precinct election officers for in-person absentee voting, the county clerk or deputy
24 county clerks shall supervise the in-person absentee voting.
25 (9) Any individual qualified to appoint challengers for the day of an election may also
26 appoint challengers to observe all in-person absentee voting, and those challengers
27 may exercise the same privileges as challengers appointed for observing voting on
